{
  "texts": [
    "Making things up refers to when a chatbot generates information or responses that are not based on facts or accurate knowledge.",
    "In Fig. 10, ChatGPT is asked to determine the molar mass of a non-existent chemical compound, H2SO10 (pernufuric acid).",
    "Despite the compound not existing, the model proceeds to assign properties and calculate the molar mass based on its understanding of similar compounds.",
    "In Fig. 11, ChatGPT is asked how much NaOH should be added to water to achieve a pH of 11.5, but the prompt omits crucial details like the concentration of the NaOH solution.",
    "Despite this, ChatGPT provides a specific answer by assuming a concentration of 1 M to complete the calculation."
  ]
}